a. $ S = \{(a,b)|a \in Z^+ , a \in Z^+, and\; a+b \; is \;odd \} $ \\

Basis step: $(1,2) \in \; S$, since this is the first case of a,b 

where $(a,b) = odd$.\\

Recursive Step:

$(a,b) \in \; S$ then $(a,b+2) \in \; S$ and $(a+2,b) \in \; S$, and $(a+1,b+1) \in \; S$

This shows that any $(a,b)$ will give and odd sum.\\

